<h2 id="fixing-issues-with-github-modified-time">fixing issues with github modified-time</h2>

<p>When you clone, all the modified times are missing as it is not recorded in git. The way around is to use some script to match modified times with commit time (which is somewhat good enough.</p>

<p>we start <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/a/21735986/5986651">here</a> which has 2 solutions which is pointed to. We choose <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/a/13284229/5986651">this one</a>.</p>

<p><strong>check pre-reqs</strong>
<a href="https://github.com/MestreLion/git-tools#install">Pre-reqs</a></p>

<p>Need badh, python3, git</p>

<p><strong>install and run</strong></p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>sudo apt install git-restore-mtime
git restore-mtime --test
git restore-mtime #works in the folder you are in and other sub folders (GREAT)
</code></pre></div></div>

